Lonmnin Plans to Provide Jobs to Locals at Marikana, Business Report Says

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-08-29T05:45:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/lonmnin-plans-to-provide-jobs-to-locals-at-marikana-business-report-says.html
Lonmin Plc (LMI)  will provide more than
600 jobs for the Bapo Ba Mogale community that lives near its
Marikana platinum mine following protests last week, Business
Report said, citing Chief Executive Officer Ian Farmer.  Community members from Bapong in the North West province of
 South Africa  will be appointed to fill 259 vacancies and another
384 jobs will be created in the near future, the Johannesburg-
based newspaper Farmer as saying. Community members were
demanding jobs for at least 2,500 residents, it said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
